\newlabel{tab:celeba_unified_summary}{{2}{12}{\textbf {CelebA cross-modal results (CLIP ViT-B/32, 40 binary attributes).} \emph {Leakage (pp)}: signed $S - S_{\text {floor}}$ at the trajectory step closest to the per-attribute majority-class chance; $0$ = at chance, lower in absolute value = stronger erasure. \emph {@chance}: settings driven to chance ($|S{-}S_{\text {floor}}| \le 0.5$pp) over settings the method reached the budget on. Each method is run on 40 attributes under each control regime (5 least- vs.\ 5 most-correlated controls per target). The CelebA pipeline uses \TanGCEp {} (LEACE preprocessing + manifold loop); the rank-2 covariance step that yields the NLP \TanGCEpp {} headline was not run on CelebA. Best per column in \textbf {bold}. `--' = no in-budget step at that budget for that method}{table.caption.20}{}}
